# React

**Agent:** Put components and hooks in `src/features/<domain>/`; arrow components, named React imports, effects only for external sync.

## Files

| Kind | Path / name |
|------|-------------|
| Component + TSX | `src/features/<domain>/PascalCase.tsx` — `export default` |
| Custom hook | `src/features/<domain>/useName.ts` — colocated |
| Feature CSS | Colocated `.css` — master theme tokens only; no cross-feature class refs |

## Components

- `const PascalCase = (...) =>` at module top level — never nested inside another component.
- Named imports from `'react'` only — no default `React`.
- Pure render: no prop/state mutation or side effects in render body.
- Hooks before any early return; only in components or custom hooks.
- Never call a component as a function — JSX only.
- Destructure props in the parameter list — every identifier in the render body must be a destructured prop, import, or local. Fallback chains (`foo ?? bar`) require **both** names in scope; a bare prop name throws `ReferenceError`.

## Event handlers

`const handleSubmit = () => {}` — `handle` + action; arrow only per `typescript.mdc`.

## Effects — when not to use `useEffect`

| Situation | Do instead |
|-----------|------------|
| Derived value from props/state | Compute in render |
| Filtered/transformed list | Render; `useMemo` if expensive |
| User action | Event handler |
| Notify parent of child change | Parent callback in same handler |
| Reset child when prop identity changes | `key={id}` on child |
| Chained state-setting Effects | Single handler or render calc |
| Form POST on interaction | Submit handler |

**Use `useEffect` for:** external subscriptions (browser APIs, widgets), display analytics, sync outside React state. Prefer plain render calc; `useMemo` only when profiled.

## Bootstrap

Wrap root in `<StrictMode>` in `src/main.tsx`.

## Styling

Master CSS at app entry (`src/index.css` / `src/scss/theme.scss`). Co-located feature CSS may use master classes/variables only. Scrollbar theming → master CSS only. Never use inline `style`.

See `css.mdc` (tokens, surfaces, motion), `typescript.mdc` (language semantics).
